There's a currency conversion trap that most travelers and businesses fall into:
Â 
That "Pay in [card currency] or [local foreign currency]?" question isn't as innocent as it seems.
Â 
I never really understood why we should always choose foreign currency (it seems to be common knowledge but not many know why) until I went deep into fintech. Turns out, Dynamic Currency Conversion (DCC) sounds convenient (maybe even helpful) but costs travelers or businesses an average 4-10% markup through hidden fees and inflated exchange rates.
Â 
Our data at SiFi - Simplified Financial Solutions Company shows businesses are leaving money on the table in ~45% of foreign transactions.

Many online subscription services and platforms automatically default to local currency conversion or bury the option to switch, whereas payment terminals at least present the choice upfront (though customers often select the costlier option without realizing it).
Â 
The rule is simple: Always choose foreign currency and let your card handle the conversion.
Â
